Not the first time that Morris has gotten rid of Russell and the smiles among the RR players suggest that it was a matchup that they fancied. This is very full, angling into Russell who can't properly get under the loft. Ends up drilling it flat down to long-on where Miller is safe as houses. Commentary Text: Chris Morris to Tripathi, out Morgan Run Out!! Mayhem, absolute mayhem!! One of the worst ways to lose a wicket and KKR have lost their skipper. Very full delivery from Morris, Tripathi drove this sweetly and Morgan's bat got in the way of it, deflecting this towards the left of Morris. Tripathi started a run, no idea why, and Morgan wasn't clear in his communication either. Morris was alert to the situation, got to the ball quickly and raced to the non-striker's end to whip off the bails. Phew! Unbelievable stuff! Morgan run out (Chris Morris) 0(0)

Commentary Text: Unadkat to Narine, out Caught by Jaiswal!! He dropped one early on but no mistake this time. Very similar to the one that he put down but he ensures the ball does not pop out. The plan to send Narine does not work for KKR. Slower delivery banged into the surface, Narine goes for the pull and the top-edge flies backward of square leg, Jaiswal runs in and slides forward to take a good low catch. Commentary Text: Chetan Sakariya to Nitish Rana, out Caught by Samson!! Wicket right after the break. How many times have we seen that? Rana gets a start, plays out 25 balls and then throws it away. Not what KKR wanted. Short and outside off, Rana sees the width and slashes hard, the top-edge flies to Samson and he takes it over his head. There was some extra bounce and that's what defeated Rana as he was not able to cope with that. Nitish Rana c Samson b Chetan Sakariya 22(25) [4s-1 6s-1]

Commentary Text: Mustafizur to Shubman Gill, out Shubman Gill Run Out!! It was bound to happen. Gill never looked comfortable and he tries to steal a non-existent single only to find himself short of the crease. Fizz nails the yorker on off-stump, Gill jams it out towards cover and calls for the single, Buttler runs to his right, picks the ball and under-arms the throw onto the stumps - all this in one motion. Gill put in the dive and was still more than a yard short. So the drop chance early on does not cost RR much. Shubman Gill run out (Buttler) 11(19) [4s-1]

Commentary Text: Chakravarthy to Buttler, out Lbw!! Buttler has been given OUT LBW, he has a chat with his partner and off he goes. Was it bouncing over? Was it sliding down leg? Could Buttler have risked the review? Anyway, he can keep pondering in the dug-out - good comeback from Chakravarthy - drifted one with the angle and beat Buttler with the turn - the stride wasn't big and he was struck below the knee-roll, in front of middle and leg. The umpire was sure though, didn't think too long before raising the finger. Big scalp for KKR, the dangerous Buttler falls. Skimming the top of leg-stump, would have stayed with the umpire's call even if Buttler had reviewed. Buttler lbw b Chakravarthy 5(7) [4s-1]
